---
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="MUN Quant Society"
  subtitle="Director, Data & Infrastructure · Sep 2025 – Present · 11 Contributors"
  logo="/logos/mqs.png"
  logoAlt="MUN Quant Society"
  context="Team"
  tags={["Python", "PostgreSQL", "PyTorch", "Hugging Face Transformers", "GCP", "GitHub Actions", "pandas", "NumPy", "scikit-learn"]}
>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-600 text-white/80 mb-4">Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-4">
      I lead a team of <strong class="text-white/75">11 contributors</strong> as Director of Data & Infrastructure 
      for the MUN Quant Society. In this role I am responsible for the design, development, and deployment 
      of the society's full-stack quantitative trading platform. The system handles everything from 
      live market data ingestion and strategy execution to sentiment analysis and risk management, 
      all running on <strong class="text-white/75">PostgreSQL</strong> and deployed through <strong class="text-white/75">GCP</strong>.
    </p>
    <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
      Below is a breakdown of each major system I built or directed the development of, 
      along with the technical decisions, outcomes, and tools involved.
    </p>
    <a href="https://github.com/MUNQuantSociety/MQSMaster" target="_blank" class="detail-link mt-3 inline-block">View on GitHub →</a>
  </section>

  <!-- System Architecture Diagram -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-600 text-white/80 mb-6">System Architecture</h2>
    <div class="glass-card p-6 mb-4">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-dashed border-white/10 p-8 text-center text-sm text-white/25 font-mono">
        Add architecture diagram: /public/projects/mqs/architecture.png
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Live Trading Engine -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-600 text-white/80 mb-6">What I Built</h2>
    <div class="space-y-8">

      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85">Live Trading Engine</h3>
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <span class="tech-tag">Python</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Threading</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">PostgreSQL</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Architected a <strong class="text-white/70">concurrent multi-portfolio trading engine</strong> 
          to allow the society to run multiple strategies at once without them interfering with each 
          other. Each portfolio runs in its own thread with a configurable polling interval, pulling 
          the latest market data and portfolio state before generating trade signals.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <li>
            Built <strong class="text-white/70">atomic state queries</strong> using PostgreSQL CTEs 
            so that every strategy sees a consistent snapshot of its cash and positions at the time 
            of each decision, preventing race conditions across concurrent threads.
          </li>
          <li>
            Implemented a <strong class="text-white/70">circuit breaker pattern</strong> that tracks 
            consecutive failures per portfolio and automatically halts any strategy thread after 5 
            failures, isolating problems so one broken strategy cannot cascade into others.
          </li>
          <li>
            Designed a <strong class="text-white/70">thread-safe connection pool</strong> 
            (minconn=1, maxconn=6) to manage concurrent database access efficiently across all 
            portfolio threads without connection exhaustion.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Backtesting -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85">Backtesting Framework</h3>
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <span class="tech-tag">Python</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">pandas</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">NumPy</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Developed a <strong class="text-white/70">backtesting engine</strong> that allows the 
          team to validate any trading strategy against historical data before deploying it live. 
          Supports both an event-driven mode (simulates real market conditions bar-by-bar) and a 
          faster vectorized mode for rapid iteration.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <li>
            Built the <strong class="text-white/70">BacktestRunner</strong>, an event-driven 
            simulator that groups historical data by timestamp, applies configurable slippage 
            models, and feeds each strategy a sliding lookback window to replicate how data 
            arrives in real-time trading.
          </li>
          <li>
            Created a <strong class="text-white/70">BacktestExecutor</strong> with a full margin 
            model supporting long and short positions with configurable leverage (default 2x), 
            mirroring live trading constraints so backtests produce realistic results.
          </li>
          <li>
            Automated <strong class="text-white/70">12 report types per backtest run</strong>: 
            trade logs, performance timeseries, Sharpe ratio, max drawdown, rolling statistics 
            (30/90/180-day windows), monthly return breakdowns, benchmark comparisons against 
            buy-and-hold, and portfolio risk analytics including correlation matrices.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Strategy API -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85">Strategy API & Indicator System</h3>
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <span class="tech-tag">Python</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">OOP</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Designed a <strong class="text-white/70">plug-and-play strategy framework</strong> that 
          lets any team member write a new trading strategy in under 50 lines of code, without 
          needing to understand the underlying database, execution, or data infrastructure.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <li>
            Built an <strong class="text-white/70">abstract BasePortfolio class</strong> that 
            provides a clean StrategyContext API with access to market data (OHLCV, historical 
            lookback), portfolio state (cash, positions, weights), and simple buy/sell methods 
            with confidence-weighted position sizing.
          </li>
          <li>
            Developed a <strong class="text-white/70">dynamic indicator factory</strong> using 
            Python's importlib, so indicators are registered by name and automatically loaded at 
            runtime. Created <strong class="text-white/70">7 built-in indicators</strong>: SMA, 
            RSI, Relative Momentum Index, ATR, Displaced Moving Average, Rate of Change, and VWAP, 
            each with automatic warmup from historical data.
          </li>
          <li>
            Enabled the team to deploy <strong class="text-white/70">4 live strategies</strong>: 
            VolMomentum, MomentumStrategy, RegimeAdaptiveStrategy, and TrendRotateStrategy, all 
            running concurrently through the live engine.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- NLP Pipeline -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85">NLP Sentiment Analysis Pipeline</h3>
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <span class="tech-tag">PyTorch</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Hugging Face</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">FinBERT</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Built and deployed a <strong class="text-white/70">real-time news sentiment pipeline</strong> 
          that scrapes financial articles, scores them using a fine-tuned transformer model, and 
          feeds the results directly into the trading strategies for signal enrichment.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <li>
            Developed a <strong class="text-white/70">multi-source news scraper</strong> that pulls 
            articles from FMP, Yahoo Finance, Finviz, and Alpha Vantage. Articles are deduplicated, 
            merged into per-ticker CSVs, and processed in <strong class="text-white/70">batched 
            ticker groups every 5 minutes</strong> via a daemon process, with staggered 2-minute 
            intervals between batches to respect API rate limits.
          </li>
          <li>
            Fine-tuned the <strong class="text-white/70">FinBERT model</strong> (yiyanghkust/finbert-tone) 
            on a combined dataset of Financial PhraseBank and FiQA sentiment data to improve accuracy 
            on real financial news. Trained using Hugging Face Trainer with 
            <strong class="text-white/70">AdamW optimizer</strong>, a learning rate of 
            <strong class="text-white/70">2e-5</strong>, linear learning rate scheduler with 
            <strong class="text-white/70">500 warmup steps</strong>, batch size of 18, 
            <strong class="text-white/70">5 epochs</strong>, and weight decay of 0.01. 
            Evaluated using weighted F1, precision, recall, and accuracy metrics per epoch, 
            with early stopping based on validation loss.
          </li>
          <li>
            Designed the sentiment scoring to output a value from 
            <strong class="text-white/70">-1.0 (bearish) to +1.0 (bullish)</strong> per article, 
            computed as the difference between positive and negative class probabilities from the 
            model's softmax output. Daily averages are precomputed and stored in a PostgreSQL 
            news_sentiment table for real-time access by any strategy.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-dashed border-white/10 p-6 text-center text-sm text-white/25 font-mono mt-4">
          Add screenshots: sentiment dashboard, training curves, example scores
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Data Pipeline -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85">Data Pipeline & Database</h3>
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <span class="tech-tag">PostgreSQL</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">FMP API</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">SQL</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Designed and built the <strong class="text-white/70">data infrastructure</strong> that 
          every other system in the platform depends on, from market data ingestion to trade 
          record-keeping.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <li>
            Built the <strong class="text-white/70">FMPMarketData client</strong> with a 
            thread-safe sliding-window rate limiter (3,000 requests/minute), automatic retry 
            logic (6 attempts with backoff), timeout handling (10s), and internet connectivity 
            checks to ensure reliable data ingestion across all threads.
          </li>
          <li>
            Developed a <strong class="text-white/70">backfill service</strong> that generates 
            business day ranges, batches API calls (3 days per request), caches results to CSV, 
            and bulk-inserts into PostgreSQL with conflict handling to prevent duplicate records.
          </li>
          <li>
            Defined a <strong class="text-white/70">5-table database schema</strong>: 
            market_data (OHLCV), cash_equity_book (portfolio balances), positions_book (holdings), 
            trade_execution_logs (fill records with slippage tracking), and pnl_book (portfolio 
            valuation history). All portfolio state reads use CTE-based atomic queries for consistency.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-dashed border-white/10 p-6 text-center text-sm text-white/25 font-mono mt-4">
          Add screenshots: database schema diagram, PgAdmin tables
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Risk Management -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85">Risk Management & Capital Allocation</h3>
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <span class="tech-tag">Python</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">PostgreSQL</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Built the <strong class="text-white/70">capital management layer</strong> that controls 
          how money flows between the master account and individual strategy portfolios, ensuring 
          each strategy gets its target allocation and no single strategy can over-concentrate risk.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <li>
            Implemented a <strong class="text-white/70">DailyAllocator</strong> that rebalances 
            capital across strategy portfolios every day based on configurable target weights 
            (e.g. 30%/30%/40%). The allocator calculates each portfolio's total value 
            (cash + marked-to-market positions), compares against target, and executes internal 
            transfers as paired database entries.
          </li>
          <li>
            Created a <strong class="text-white/70">CLI-based capital management tool</strong> for 
            adding and withdrawing funds from the master portfolio, with balance validation and 
            full audit logging through the trade_execution_logs table.
          </li>
          <li>
            Designed all capital transfers as <strong class="text-white/70">atomic database 
            transactions</strong>, ensuring that if any step fails mid-transfer, no partial 
            state is left behind.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- OMS -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85">Order Management System (In Progress)</h3>
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <span class="tech-tag">System Design</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Python</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Currently designing an <strong class="text-white/70">Order Management System</strong> to 
          replace the platform's fire-and-forget execution model with a proper order lifecycle. 
          The goal is to reduce market impact on large orders by slicing them over time using 
          execution algorithms.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <li>
            Designed a <strong class="text-white/70">parent/child order architecture</strong> where 
            a strategy's intent (e.g. "buy AAPL with 80% confidence") becomes a parent order that 
            is broken into smaller child orders dispatched over time.
          </li>
          <li>
            Specifying <strong class="text-white/70">VWAP and TWAP execution algorithms</strong> 
            that schedule child orders based on volume profiles and time intervals, along with 
            an OrderTracker for full lifecycle visibility (pending, partially filled, complete, 
            cancelled).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- CI/CD -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85">CI/CD & Testing</h3>
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <span class="tech-tag">GitHub Actions</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">pytest</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
          Set up <strong class="text-white/70">GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines</strong> for 
          automated testing on every push. Wrote and maintained a 
          <strong class="text-white/70">pytest test suite</strong> covering the backtest engine, 
          strategy API endpoints, trade execution, vectorized backtesting, and indicator 
          correctness. Configured test fixtures with database mocking so tests run without 
          needing a live PostgreSQL connection.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>